                        <h2>Why Replace Your 6.0 Powerstroke Oil Cooler?</h2>
                        <p class="text-lead">The factory oil cooler is one of the most common failure points on 6.0 Powerstroke engines, often leading to expensive repairs:</p>
                        <ul class="feature-list">
                            <li>Factory coolers clog easily, reducing oil flow by up to 40%</li>
                            <li>Poor cooling leads to overheating and engine damage</li>
                            <li>Failed coolers can cause EGR cooler failure ($1,200+ repair)</li>
                            <li>Oil temperature spikes damage turbos and injectors</li>
                            <li>Coolant contamination leads to head gasket failure</li>
                            <li>Average repair cost exceeds $3,000 when neglected</li>
